      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 848: The retry timer keeps running after the connection attempt progresses to ICE/connection success unless a peer response path cancels it. If `waitingForPeerResponse_` is cleared outside `onPeerResponse()` or the attempt completes/fails before the next retry tick, the timer can still fire and unnecessarily retain `devicePk`/`value` until then. Cancel and reset `answerRetryTimer_` in the common completion/cleanup path where `waitingForPeerResponse_` is cleared, not only in `onPeerResponse()`.\n```suggestion\nif (info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_) {\n    info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_-\u003ecancel();\n    info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_.reset();\n}\n```",
